  "text": "Although Mg 2+ has been reported to affect TSase activity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the mechanism has not been investigated until recently [CITATION_3] . In order to correlate the kinetic effects of Mg 2+ with their structural and dynamic origins, two X-ray crystallographic structures (PDB IDs 2G80, 4IW5 and 4ISK) were re-analyzed. Due to the differences in the stereochemistry of each inhibitor's glutamyl moiety, the possible Mg 2+ sites in the ternary complex of TSase differ in these crystal structures. However, in both cases the cation, Mg 2+ was identified near the glutamyl moiety of the folate cofactor of TSase, ca. 16 Å away from the active site [CITATION_4] .",
